        <h1 id="title">Desmond Thomas Doss</h1>
        <p>A Hero Without a Weapon</p>
        <figure id="img-div">
            <img src="https://trendingamerican.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/cover-photo-2.webp" alt="Desmond Doss receiving the Medal of Honor" id="image">
            <figcaption id="img-caption">Desmond Doss receiving the Medal of Honor from President Harry S. Truman.</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <div id="tribute-info">
            <h2>Here's a timeline of Desmond Doss's life:</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>1919</strong> - Born in Lynchburg, Virginia</li>
                <li><strong>1942</strong> - Drafted into the U.S. Army during World War II</li>
                <li><strong>1945</strong> - During the Battle of Okinawa, he rescued 75 wounded soldiers, braving enemy fire without a weapon</li>
                <li><strong>1945</strong> - Awarded the Medal of Honor by President Harry S. Truman for his extraordinary bravery</li>
                <li><strong>1990</strong> - Suffers injuries, including broken arm, when driving his car and has to be hospitalized</li>
                <li><strong>2006</strong> - Dies at his home in Piedmont, Alabama, at the age of 87</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
                "Desmond Doss was a true American hero who demonstrated extraordinary courage and faith in the face of extreme adversity."
            </p>
        </div>
